  "title": "Site Engineer",
  "description": "<h3><strong>Key Responsibilities</strong></h3>\n<ul>\n  <li><strong>Project Planning:</strong> Develop detailed plans, timelines, and resource schedules to support project execution.</li>\n  <li><strong>Technical Execution:</strong> Oversee design, development, implementation, and resolve technical issues as needed.</li>\n  <li><strong>Communication:</strong> Lead and coordinate cross-functional teams; liaise with clients, contractors, and subcontractors. Provide regular progress updates and ensure effective collaboration.</li>\n  <li><strong>Safety and Quality Control:</strong> Ensure all deliverables meet defined safety, environmental, and quality standards.</li>\n</ul>\n<h3><strong>Job Requirements</strong></h3>\n<ul>\n  <li>Minimum Diploma in Engineering (Civil / Mechanical / Electrical or equivalent).</li>\n  <li>Able to perform <strong>rotational day and night shifts</strong> due to the nature of tunnel and roadwork projects (in compliance with MOM’s work-hour and rest regulations).</li>\n  <li>Good communication, problem-solving, and teamwork skills.</li>\n  <li><strong>On-the-job training</strong> provided for fresh graduates and mid-career candidates looking to transition into the construction sector.</li>\n</ul>\n<h3><strong>Additional Information</strong></h3>\n<ul>\n  <li>Remuneration will be commensurate with qualifications and experience.</li>\n  <li>Firstcom Engineering is an <strong>equal opportunity employer</strong> committed to fair and inclusive hiring practices.</li>\n</ul>",
